news.title: Ludhiana civic body demolishes 13 illegal under-construction buildings
news.para: LMC's building branch officials claimed that the buildings were being constructed in violation of building bylaws and the owners also failed to get the building plans approved from the the civic body.

news.title: Not house, but rooftop size to matter for free solar plants in Chandigarh
news.para: There is no bar on the size of residential unit where installation can be done under the model, but the Crest has specified the minimum rooftop area and the existing electricity connection load required.

news.title: Orient Cement's MoU With Adani Power Maharashtra terminated
news.para: Orient Cement and Adani Power Maharashtra's MoU was for setting out the understanding for facilitating bona fide use of land identified for exploring the possibility of establishing a cement grinding unit (CGU) at Tiroda, Maharashtra.

news.title: HDIL promoters booked for fraud by Mumbai EOW
news.para: They are accused of duping a company by illegally selling office units in a building in suburban Andheri, said a police official here.

news.title: Property tax to be imposed in municipal areas in Jammu & Kashmir from April 1
news.para: "In exercise of the power conferred by section 71A of the Jammu and Kashmir Municipal Act 2000, the government hereby notifies the rules for levy, assessment and collection of property tax in the municipalities and municipal councils of the Union Territory," Housing and Urban Development Department Principal Secretary H Rajesh Prasad said in a notification.

news.title: Vasu Constructions booked for Rs 3 crore fraud in Panchkula
news.para: Balbir Singh, a resident of Sector 10, Ambala, told police that he was contacted by Vasu Constructions company owned by Satish Monga, Ravi Monga and Aryana Monga, all residents of Sector 20, in July 2020.

news.title: Truck operators returned to work in Himachal Pradesh after sixty-eight days
news.para: The deadlock between the cement company management and truck operators ended on Monday after both the management of the Adani cement plants and the representatives of the truck unions agreed to the new freight rate of Rs 10.30 per kilometre per tonne for single axle and Rs 9.30 per kilometre per tonne for multi-axle.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Construction on plots in town planning scheme 204 gets nod
news.para: The state urban development department has issued orders to the Ahmedabad municipal commissioner and the town planning officer to approve construction plans in all the “final” plots on TP Scheme 204 spread over 1,121.19 hectares.

news.title: Cement demand to continue uptrend with 7-9% rise next fiscal: Crisil
news.para: However, the outlook on operating margin, which has been under pressure, remains clouded with the prices of key inputs – coal and pet-coke – remaining elevated. This will have a bearing on the credit risk profiles of players.

news.title: UT estate office sends property details to Chandigarh civic body
news.para: The data has details like name of the property owner, status and nature of the property, etc. Information of properties in multiple categories, including residential, commercial, institutional have been sent to the MC.

news.title: Goa cabinet approves amendment to save certain unauthorised structures
news.para: The ordinance will stop authorised officers from rejecting applications for regularisation of unauthorised structures on the grounds that the applicant does not have the consent of the co-owner of the house despite the property or land already being legally divided.

news.title: Bhopal civic body pulls up contractor under PMAY project
news.para: BMC commissioner KVS Choudhary directed officials action against the private contractor. Construction sites at Rahul Nagar, opposite BMC HQ at Mata Mandir were inspected by BMC official.

news.title: Now, Chandigarh housing board's no dues certificate available on website
news.para: ​At present, allottees/applicants are required to submit an application for NDC before applying for various services like transfer of units/mutation/mortgage permissions etc.

news.title: Clear lease amount by March 5: Rajasthan housing board
news.para: “Consumers after taking over several institutional and commercial assets from the housing board have not cleared the outstanding lease amount. Under such circumstances, the board is losing a huge revenue,” said housing commissioner Pawan Arora.

news.title: Delhi civic body starts drive over property tax dues
news.para: MCD targets to collect Rs 3,850 crore in property tax in the financial year 2022-23 and only Rs 1,671 crore has been collected. Last year, it collected around Rs 2,000 crore.
